What is Kanban View?

Definition:

Kanban View displays records as visual cards. It helps users quickly see and manage records without opening each one.

In your case, each card represents a Sales Quotation.

Screen Explanation
1. Module Name

At the top left:

Sales

This indicates you are working in the Sales module.

2. Menu
Orders
To Invoice
Products
Reporting
Configuration

These are the main menus of the Sales module.

Orders → Quotations and Sales Orders.
To Invoice → Orders ready for invoicing.
Products → Product master data.
Reporting → Sales reports and analytics.
Configuration → Sales settings.
3. Quotation Cards (Kanban Cards)

Each rectangle is a Kanban Card.

You have two cards.

Card 1
XYZ Retail

This is the Customer Name.

Below that:

₹15,000.00

This is the Quotation Total Amount.

Next line:

S00002

This is the Quotation Number.

Every quotation has a unique number.

Next:

07/07/2026 12:50:33

This is the Creation Date & Time.

Blue badge:

Quotation

This indicates the current status.

Possible statuses include:

Quotation
Quotation Sent
Sales Order
Cancelled
Card 2

Customer:

ABC Technologies

Quotation Number:

S00001

Amount:

₹2,000.00

Status:

Quotation
4. Company Filter

At the top search bar:

Company is
Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd

This filter shows only quotations belonging to Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd.

If you change it to Ravinder Retail Pvt Ltd, you'll see only that company's quotations.

5. View Icons (Top Right)

You can switch between different ways of displaying the same data.

List View

Displays data in rows and columns.

Example:

Quotation No | Customer | Amount

Best for working with many records.

Kanban View (Current)

Displays records as cards.

Best for a quick visual overview.

Calendar View

Shows quotations by date.

Useful for tracking due dates.

Pivot View

Summarizes data.

Example:

Total Sales
Sales by Customer
Sales by Month
Graph View

Displays charts.

Examples:

Bar Chart
Pie Chart
Line Chart

Useful for presentations and analysis.

Activity View

Shows scheduled activities.

Examples:

Calls
Meetings
Follow-ups

Helps users track pending tasks.

Advantages of Kanban View
Easy to understand.
Visual representation.
Quick access to records.
Open a record with one click.
Good for sales teams.
Real-World Example

Imagine a sales manager.

Instead of reading a table with 100 quotations, they can quickly look at the cards and immediately identify:

Customer name
Amount
Status
Creation date

This makes it easier to monitor ongoing sales work.

Interview Question
What is Kanban View in Odoo?

Answer:

Kanban View is a visual card-based view used to display records. Each card represents one record, allowing users to quickly view important information and open or manage records easily.

